Creating a handicraft product that would be competitive in contemporary consumerist and  marketing environment, and choosing for it an appropriate distribution channel. The students develop a unique or small-scale production handicraft product and its production guidelines. Performing the preparatory stages for production, leading the production process and marketing.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To create an craft product or product line that is competitive in the consumer and marketing environment. Students will select the optimum method for executing the product or series; individual, small-scale commercial production or a combination thereof.
They will think of a suitable target group and sales channel as well.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students - will know the modern handicraft market situation and is demands, the specifics of products; - will know the various consumer groups and needs thereof; - will be capable of creating various products and product groups, being able, drawing on their knowledge and skills, to lead the market situation and consumer demands.
